  "description": "R5: `Consent.regulatoryBasis`",
  "purpose": "This extension is part of the cross-version definitions generated to enable use of the\r\nelement `Consent.regulatoryBasis` as defined in FHIR R5\r\nin FHIR R4.\r\n\r\nThe source element is defined as:\r\n`Consent.regulatoryBasis` 0..* `CodeableConcept`\r\n\r\nAcross FHIR versions, the element set has been mapped as:\r\n*  R5: `Consent.regulatoryBasis` 0..* `CodeableConcept`\n*  R4B: `Consent.policyRule` 0..1 `CodeableConcept`\n*  R4: `Consent.policyRule` 0..1 `CodeableConcept`\r\n\r\nFollowing are the generation technical comments:\r\nElement `Consent.regulatoryBasis` allows multiple values in the source, but is mapped to an element that does not allow multiple values in the target.\nElement `Consent.regulatoryBasis` is mapped to FHIR R4 element `Consent.policyRule` as `SourceIsBroaderThanTarget`.",
